solutions.content:
If a character is at boundry, there is not point in moving it towards center.
At any given moment, there can be 2 option for making the boundry palindrome.
Choose the one with minimum value greedily and keep updating the string.

```
class Solution {
    public int minMovesToMakePalindrome(String s) {
        int count = 0;

        while(s.length() > 2) {
            char ch1 = s.charAt(0);
            int len = s.length();
            char ch2 = s.charAt(len - 1);

            if (ch1 == ch2) {
                s = s.substring(1, len - 1);
            } else {
                int id1 = s.lastIndexOf(ch1);
                int id2 = s.indexOf(ch2);

                int steps1 = len - id1 - 1;
                int steps2 = id2;

                StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

                if (steps1 > steps2) {
                    count += steps2;
                    sb.append(s.substring(0, id2));
                    sb.append(s.substring(id2 + 1, len - 1));
                } else {
                    count += steps1;
                    sb.append(s.substring(1, id1));
                    sb.append(s.substring(id1 + 1));
                }

                s = sb.toString();
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
}
```

