solutions.content:
**Hello guys,**
this is a simple solution for  `Minimum Number of Moves to Make Palindrome` problem

Let `l=0, r=n-1`

`if(s[l]==s[r]) l++,r--;`

`else`
`{`
search s[l] from right side of the string 
and seach s[r] from left side of the string

let we get `s[l]` at `idx2` from right then there will be` r-idx2` swaps required
and for we get `s[r]` at `idx1` from left then there will be `idx1-l` swaps required

we will take swap action from min distance and pull that particular character to `l` or `r`
`}`

**Code:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minMovesToMakePalindrome(string s) {

        int n=s.size();
        int l=0,r=n-1;

        int cnt=0;
        while(l<r)
        {
            if(s[l]==s[r])
            {
                l++,r--;
            }
            else
            {
                int idx1=l,idx2=r;

                // left search
                char c=s[r];
                for(int i=l+1;i<n;++i)
                {
                    if(s[i]==c)
                    {
                        idx1=i; break;
                    }
                }

                // right search
                c=s[l];
                for(int i=r-1;i>=0;i--)
                {
                    if(s[i]==c) {
                        idx2=i; break;
                    }
                }

                // swap 
                if(idx1-l<=r-idx2)
                {
                    while(idx1>l)
                    {
                        swap(s[idx1],s[idx1-1]);
                        idx1--;

                        cnt++;
                    }
                }
                else
                {
                    while(idx2<r)
                    {
                        swap(s[idx2], s[idx2+1]);
                        idx2++;

                        cnt++;
                    }
                }

                l++,r--;
            }
        }

        return cnt;
    }
};
```

