# Intuition + Approach
- We basically try to convert the second half of the string into the first half.
- To do this, We greedily pick the closest element to the right pointer and swap it until we reach its correct position, i..e.. (n-i-1).
- An edge case will be when the length of the string is odd and there's a character which occurs an odd number of times, and then this odd character should be present in the middle of the whole string.
- To do this, if the character is found at the same index as the left pointer, then we just shift it by one to the right,so that it comes in the middle eventually.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n*n) worst case
