# Intuition
two pointer approach: inititalize two pointers to the start of the array and the end of the array respectively, and then check if they are the same, if they arent, move the right backwards and find the same charater in the array, and swap the adjacent characters till it reaches the correct spot, performing a final swap in the middle of the array at the end while ensure the correct answer 

# Approach
1) convert it to character array
2) use count variable to track the number of swaps
3) initialise two pointers let and right, and also a "find" variable to find the character which is same as the character in the position "left" 
4) after finding the character, swap it with adjacent characters until you reach the right index.
5) perform these oprations until you reach the middle of the array, at the middle of the array, swap the adjacent elements to get the required answer

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n^2) 

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minMovesToMakePalindrome(String s) {
        int count=0;
        char[] charArray=s.toCharArray();
        int right=charArray.length-1;
        int left=0;
        int find=0;
        while(left<right){
            find=right;// the find variable to find the same character as left
            if(charArray[left]==charArray[right]){
                left++;// if at the right position, move the pointers
                right--;
            }else{


                while(charArray[find]!=charArray[left]){
                    find--;// move the find pointer backwards until you find the right spot
                }
                if(left==find){
                    swap(charArray,find,find+1);
                    count++;continue;// for middle of the array
                }else{
                while((find)<right){
                    swap(charArray,find,find+1);
                    find+=1;count+=1;// for moving the find variable value to the correct spot by swapping adjacent element until it reaches the "right" index. update he counter for every swap                }}

            }

        }
        return count;


    }
    public void swap(char[] c,int a,int b){
        char temp=c[a];
        c[a]=c[b];
        c[b]=temp;
    }

}
```

