# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
The approach used in this code is to traverse the string from both ends simultaneously and comparing the characters. If the characters are not the same, we need to perform a swap operation to make them equal. If the string has odd length and we reach the middle of the string, we need to handle the middle element differently by swapping it with the adjacent element. We continue this process until we reach the middle of the string.

# Complexity
The time complexity of this algorithm is O(n^2) where n is the length of the string s because we are traversing the string multiple times. The space complexity is O(1) because we are not using any additional data structure to store the string or intermediate results.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minMovesToMakePalindrome(string s) {
        int n = s.length();

        int left = 0, right = s.size() - 1, ans = 0;

        // Traverse the string from both ends simultaneously
        while (left < right) {
            int l = left, r = right;

            // Compare the characters at left and right positions
            while (s[l] != s[r]) {
                r--;   
            }

            // If l==r, we have reached the odd middle element of the string
            if (l == r) {
                // Swap the middle element with the adjacent element
                swap(s[r], s[r + 1]);
                ans++;
                continue;
            } 
            else {
                // If l!=r, we have reached a normal element
                // Move the unequal character to the right side of the string
                while (r < right) {
                    swap(s[r], s[r + 1]);
                    ans++;
                    r++;
                }
            }
            // Move to the next set of left and right characters
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        // Return the number of moves required to make the string a palindrome
        return ans;
    }
};

```

