solutions.content:
Just maintain two pointers for the String,
For every character at position i there has got to be a corresponding char at pos j same as that of i so we find this char towrads the left of j and when we find it we bring this at position j and increment the number of swaps accordingly.
If we do not find any other char to the left of j other than i itself this means that the char at i occurs just once and this will inturn be the middle character of the palindrome so we swap it with i+1 th char and move forward.


```
class Solution {
    public int minMovesToMakePalindrome(String s) {
        char[] arr=s.toCharArray();
        int ans=0;

        for(int i=0;i<s.length()/2;i++){
            int j=s.length()-1-i;

            while(arr[i]!=arr[j]){
                j--;
            }
             int swaps=0;
            if(j==i){ //condn where char at i will be middle elem.
                char c=arr[i];
                arr[i]=arr[i+1];
                arr[i+1]=c;
                swaps++;
                i--;
            }else{

            for(int x=j;x<s.length()-1-i;x++){
                arr[x]=arr[x+1];
                swaps++;
            }
            arr[s.length()-1-i]=arr[i];
            }
            ans+=swaps;


        }

        return ans;
    }
}
