solutions.content:
**Elimination of TLE after 3 times Dijkastra :**

* Generally while running Dijkastra algorithm, we often forget to check that if some node has lower distance than its current cost, we can ignore processing that node.
i.e. if  **dis[u] < cost (where cost = pq.top().first & u = pq.top().second)** then we can stop processing that node.

* And doing that only, we eliminate TLE. 
* This is a good problem, worth solving and checking the actual runtime complexity of Dijkastras.

```
#define ll long long 
#define maxi 1e18
class Solution {
public:
    void solve(int src,vector<vector<pair<ll,ll>>>&graph,vector<ll>&dis)
    {
        priority_queue<pair<ll,ll>,vector<pair<ll,ll>>,greater<pair<ll,ll>>>pq;
        dis[src]=0;
        pq.push({0,src});
        while(!pq.empty())
        {
            int node=pq.top().second;
            int distance=pq.top().first;
            pq.pop();



            /* TLE Elimination */
            if(distance>dis[node])
                continue;
            /* Without above Check u will get TLE */

            for(auto itr:graph[node])
