# Intuition
- If we were asked to find the answer from `src1` and `src2` independently, then we would have applied dijkstra indivisually.
- So for this question, there can be a possibility that the path from `src1 to dest` and the path from `src2 to dest` would share some of the edges or they can be completely different.
- Using this we approach towards the solution of the problem.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Use dijkstra for each of the src1, src2, dest.
- First dijkstra store the distance of each node from `src1`.
- Second dijkstra store the distance of each node from `src2`.
- Third dijkstra use another adjacency list with reversed edge direction to store the distance of each node from `dest`.
- Finally, the answer is the minimum of these three distances for every node from `0 <= i <= N`.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N * log N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
#define ll long long
#define pii pair<ll,ll>
#define inf (1ll << 60)
class Solution {
public:
    void dijkstra(int src, vector<ll> &dist, vector<vector<pii>> &adj) {
        priority_queue<pii, vector<pii>, greater<pii>> pq;
        dist[src] = 0;
        pq.push({0,src});

        while(!pq.empty())
        {
            auto [wt,v] = pq.top();
            pq.pop();

            if(wt != dist[v])
                continue;

            for(auto [u,d] : adj[v])
            {
                if(dist[u] > wt + d)
                {
                    dist[u] = wt + d;
                    pq.push({dist[u],u});
                }
            }
        }
    }

    long long minimumWeight(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges, int src1, int src2, int dest) {
        vector<vector<pii>> adj(n,vector<pii>());
        vector<vector<pii>> radj(n,vector<pii>());
        for(auto it : edges)
        {
            int u = it[0], v = it[1], w = it[2];
            adj[u].push_back({v,w});
            radj[v].push_back({u,w});
        }

        vector<ll> dist1(n,inf), dist2(n,inf), dist3(n,inf);

        dijkstra(src1,dist1,adj);
        dijkstra(src2,dist2,adj);
        dijkstra(dest,dist3,radj);

        if(dist1[dest]==inf || dist2[dest]==inf)
            return -1;

        ll ans = inf;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
        {
            ll d = dist1[i] + dist2[i] + dist3[i];
            ans = min(ans, d);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

