**minimum weight sum of subgraph = minimum value for all N where    { minimum distance from source 1 to i + minimum distance from source 2 to i + minimum distance from i to destination }**

**minimum distance between any two nodes can be found by dijkstra if we no one node is fixed.
Here we have three fixed nodes.**

CPP Approach using Eager Dijkstra 
Optimised using Map
**Time Complexity : O(NlogN)**
**Space Complexity : O(N*N)**

	class Solution {
	public:
		const long long oo = 1e18;
		void dijkstra(int &src, vector<vector<pair<int,long long>>>&graph,vector<long long> &dist){
			map<int ,long long> pq;
			pq.insert({src,0});
			dist[src] = 0;
			while(!pq.empty()){
				int node = pq.begin()->first;
				pq.erase(node);
				for(auto [nb,wt] : graph[node]){
					if(dist[nb] > dist[node]+ wt){
						dist[nb] = dist[node] + wt;
						if(pq.count(nb))
							pq.erase(nb);
						pq.insert({nb,dist[nb]});
					}
				}
			}
		}

