# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We want the sum of paths from src1 and src2 to dest to be min. So, there are 3 possibilities of paths, i.e. 
1. min dist path from src1 to src2 and then min dist path from src2 to dest
2. min dist path from src2 to src1 and then min dist path from src1 to dest
3. min dist path from src1 and src2 to an intermediate node 'x' and then min dist path from 'x' to dest.

So, apply Dijkstras 3 times. One from src1, other from src2 and third from dest(on reversing the dges of the graph).

Then, find minimum among all three path possibilities.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n+e)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(n+e)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
