I had the idea to calculate the shortest path from src1 to dest and also from src2 to dest but couldn't figure out how to take advantage of overlapping paths. The solution is calculate also the shortest path from dest. Then, for each `i`, we visualize all 3 nodes meeting at that node, and find the `i` where the `dist[i]` from all 3 sources are minimized.
# Code
