Tips:
If we can find paths that can visit from src1 and src2 both to dest, there must exist those common nodes that:

1. We can visit this node both from src1 and src2;
2. We can visit from this node to dest.(equal to visit from dest to this node, we use reversed graph in solution to save time)
3. The total path = src1->node + src2->node + node->dest. Specially, this node can be src1, src2, dest, then part 1/2/3 will be 0.
4. There may exist more than one common node, we need find the shorest path by checking all valid common nodes.

